<h2><span id="4...g5">4...g5</span></h2>
<p>This is the Lasker variation, the most aggressive and double edged line. Black now threatens g4 followed by Qh4+, Bxg4+, and mate to follow. The most common move, and, according to Lakdawala, "Our only hope of wresting the advantage". The game now turns into a full-blown firefight.
</p>
